# Trivy ignores for vulnerabilities we cannot immediately patch.
# Each entry must cite the reason and a target resolution date.

# x402 0.2.1 -> 2.x requires re-integrating the billing flow (the
# `create_facilitator_config` and `require_payment` imports changed).
# Schedule: re-test and upgrade in the next sprint after Binance listing.
GHSA-qr2g-p6q7-w82m

# protobuf 4.25.9 -> 5.x/6.x is a major-version transitive bump pulled
# by multiple ML deps (sentence-transformers, google-generativeai, etc).
# Risk of breaking those takes the change out of scope for a point
# release. Tracked for the Q2 2026 dep refresh sprint.
CVE-2026-0994

# wheel 0.45.1 -> 0.46.2 is a build-time tool shipped inside the image
# but only used by pip at install time; the privilege escalation CVE
# requires a malicious .whl to be installed at runtime, which we do
# not do. Tracked for the Q2 2026 dep refresh sprint.
CVE-2026-24049

# astropy FITS processing CVE — astropy not actually used in runtime
# paths (transitive via a scientific computing dep). Low practical risk.
CVE-2026-40192

# starlette Range header DoS — fastapi 0.115.12 gates starlette to
# <0.47 so the fixed version (0.49.1) cannot be installed without
# upgrading fastapi, which carries breaking-change risk right before
# a Binance listing. Tracked for the same Q2 2026 refresh as x402.
# Attacker needs to send crafted HTTP Range headers; we do not serve
# user-controlled range requests so practical exposure is low.
CVE-2025-62727

# urllib3 decompression-bomb CVEs — fixed in 2.6.3 but cdp-sdk 1.33.2
# gates urllib3 to <=2.3.0. Coinbase's cdp-sdk is coupled to the x402
# SDK version (same team, shared breaking changes at v2), so upgrading
# cdp-sdk is the same migration as x402. Deferred to Q2 2026.
# Exposure: decompression bombs require attacker-controlled response
# bodies; our outbound calls go only to known API hosts.
CVE-2025-66418
CVE-2025-66471
CVE-2026-21441

# jaraco.context path traversal — transitive via setuptools/packaging;
# upgrading the full setuptools chain is risky. The CVE needs attacker-
# controlled tar archives at install time, not runtime. Build images
# are immutable so exposure after deploy is zero. Deferred to Q2 2026.
CVE-2026-23949

# pyasn1 unbounded recursion DoS — transitive via crypto libs (pyopenssl,
# etc.). Upgrade would cascade into multiple deps. Low practical risk:
# attacker would need to feed malformed ASN.1 to us, which we do not
# do — we only parse certificates from our own TLS stack. Deferred.
CVE-2026-30922

# aiohttp auto_decompress zip-bomb — cdp-sdk 1.33.2 hard-pins
# aiohttp==3.11.16 (not a range), so this CVE cannot be patched
# without the cdp-sdk/x402 v2 migration. Outbound HTTP goes only to
# known API hosts, so an attacker would need to compromise one of
# those providers first. Deferred to Q2 2026.
CVE-2025-69223
